title: Central Statistics Office Ireland, Frequency of Persons aged 3 or over to speak Irish statistics, Ireland, 2006
name: Central Statistics Office Ireland, Frequency of Persons aged 3 or over to speak Irish statistics, Ireland, 2006
description: This dataset has data on the frequency that persons speak Irish throughout towns in Ireland that have a population of over 1000. The data includes both number and percentages for the following: Speaks Irish daily within education system only, speaks irish daily in and out of education system, outside education system daily, outside education system weekly, outside education system less often, outside education system never, and outside education system not stated. The towns have been geolocated by their lat/lon position. For more info about the data go to cso.ie/census.
